               <floruit notBefore="1912" notAfter="1969">He was a painter, poet, polemicist and historian. 
                  He received a traditional church education at the age of five in <placeName ref="LOC2981Entott"/>. After he attended traditional eduaction in various churches,
                  he became a teacher of qǝne. Then, he worked as assistant head in the customs and later as a caligrapher and illustrator at the Minsitry of Pen. 
                
                  He was also a court historian writing the royal chronicle for the period <date>1908-1934</date> covering the rules of
                  <roleName type="title">lǝg</roleName><persName ref="PRS5620IyasuV"/> and<persName ref="PRS10671Zawditu"/>. 
                 
